# Aim

To implement the quantum teleportation protocol in Qiskit, teleport an arbitrary single-qubit quantum state using an entangled Bell pair and classical communication, and verify successful teleportation through fidelity analysis.

# Objective

To understand the working principle of the quantum teleportation protocol.
To prepare an arbitrary unknown quantum state.
To create a Bell pair shared between two parties (Alice and Bob).
To teleport the unknown quantum state using entanglement and classical communication.
To simulate the teleportation protocol using Qiskit.
To verify successful teleportation by calculating the fidelity between the original and teleported states.

# Theory

Quantum teleportation is one of the fundamental protocols in quantum information science. Contrary to its name, quantum teleportation does not involve the physical transfer of a particle. Instead, it transfers the quantum state of one qubit to another distant qubit using:

Quantum entanglement
Classical communication
Local quantum operations

The protocol was first proposed by Bennett et al. (1993).

### Participants
Alice possesses:
Unknown quantum state
One qubit of an entangled Bell pair
Bob possesses:
The second qubit of the Bell pair

The unknown state is

∣ψ⟩=α∣0⟩+β∣1⟩

